snippet.textDisplay:
The problem is darksouls set the bar too high, so any game trying to cash in on that formula has to try even harder to draw a player base.

I mean Lies of P isn’t a bad idea, but you sure as heck don’t see anyone talking about it, same with every other game even remotely “dark souls”-like, comparing it instantly kills your experience, and most of the newer copy cats (not saying they stole the idea from dark souls, but you can only have so many lookalikes) either have insanely bad combat to make it feel “hard” or it straight up just copies things that make it feel boring since your going into a new game but immediately feel like you know exactly what’s going on (we don’t need “bonfires” in every single darksouls-ish game, as soon as you go and put a respawn point your character rests at that respawns all the enemies you immediately fail the originality test, darksouls made it a staple, so now when another game tries it you give darksouls players an immediate out to be annoyed, because if their not playing darksouls it’s probably because they want something NEW.

Almost every single “souls-like” I’ve seen are just blatant copies that try and make a playable game with as little effort as possible and then try and cash out on people buying it thinking their going to play something original.

Same reason people get pissed at CoD, you can only release the same exact content so many times before people eventually get annoyed, people want change, it doesn’t have to be massive, but it’s got to be enough so they feel like they are experiencing something new.

The only game I would say somewhat holds up to this is Lies Of P, yeah it takes heavy inspiration from dark souls, but it sets itself up in an entirely different way, it tells you that you can’t just brute force your way through the game, it plays into a story instead of you just being “a guy” and winging it, the atmosphere plays on a dystopian steampunk world corrupted by politics and pollution.

It does enough to give itself an identity, instead of just going “ok so your a guy and you almost died and now your magic or something good luck” 

Every other game so far has disappointed me, Lords of the fallen had a nice idea, but they just never really did anything with the whole “underworld” thing, sure it’s useful in specific places, but most people aren’t going to have fun if they need to flash a light at every single wall they see just in case there is a secret passage, just because people want to “explore” doesn’t mean they want to watch paint dry in a video game.
